The Nigerian Association of Liquified Petroleum Gas Marketers, (NALPGAM) is seeking the support of the Akwa Ibom State Government in the usage of cooking gas across the state. National President of NALPGAM, Mr. Nosa Ogieva-Okunbor, made the call during its Annual General Meeting (AGM) yesterday in Uyo. He said the support will deepen the use of Liquified Petroleum Gas in the state and create a better and healthy citizenry. Ogieva-Okunbor said the consumption level of liquefied gas in the state was low at 11,000 MT especially being the highest oil and gas producing state in the country. The wife of the state Governor Mrs. Martha Emmanuel represented by the Commissioner of Agriculture and Women Affairs, Dr. Glory Edet, thanked the team for the effort and donation of free gas cylinders to Akwa Ibom residents and mostly the women. Group to distribute N5m free gas in A/Ibom Gas marketers raise alarm on LPG skid plants in filling stations NIPCOâ€™s entry breaks monopoly in LPG business - Marketers Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin